    <language>en_US</language>
    <keyword>normpdf</keyword>
    <short_description>Normal probability density function</short_description>
    <syntax>
        <syntax_item>y = normpdf(x)</syntax_item>
        <syntax_item>y = normpdf(x, mu)</syntax_item>
        <syntax_item>y = normpdf(x, mu, sigma)</syntax_item>
    </syntax>
    <param_input>
        <param_input_item>
            <param_name>x</param_name>
            <param_description
      >scalar value or array: Values at which to evaluate pdf.</param_description>
        </param_input_item>
        <param_input_item>
            <param_name>mu</param_name>
            <param_description
      >scalar value, 0 (default) or array: Mean.</param_description>
        </param_input_item>
        <param_input_item>
            <param_name>sigma</param_name>
            <param_description
      >positive scalar value, 1 (default) or array of positive values: Standard deviation.</param_description>
        </param_input_item>
    </param_input>
    <param_output>
        <param_output_item>
            <param_name>y</param_name>
            <param_description
      >scalar value or array: pdf values.</param_description>
        </param_output_item>
    </param_output>
    <description>
        <p>
            <b
      >normpdf</b> computes the probability density function of the normal (Gaussian) distribution.
        </p>
        <p>The general formula for the normal distribution PDF is:</p>
        <latex
    >f(x|\mu,\sigma^2) = \frac{1}{\sigma\sqrt{2\pi}} e^{-\frac{(x-\mu)^2}{2\sigma^2}}</latex>
        <p>where</p>
        <latex>\mu</latex>
        <p>is the mean and</p>
        <latex>\sigma^2</latex>
        <p>is the variance.</p>
        <p>For the standard normal distribution (</p>
        <latex>\mu = 0, \sigma = 1</latex>
        <p>):</p>
        <latex>\phi(x) = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi}} e^{-\frac{x^2}{2}}</latex>
    </description>
                <used_function />
                <bibliography
  >Evans, M., N. Hastings, and B. Peacock. Statistical Distributions. 2nd ed. Hoboken, NJ: John Wiley and Sons, Inc., 1993.</bibliography>
                <examples>
                    <example_item>
                        <example_item_type>nelson</example_item_type>
                        <example_item_description />
                        <example_item_data
        runnable="cli"
      ><![CDATA[x = [-0.2, -0.1, 0, 0.1, 0.2];
R = normpdf(x);

x = [-0.2, -0.1, 0, 0.1, 0.2];
R = normpdf(x, 2, 1);

R = normpdf(0, [-0.2, -0.1, 0, 0.1, 0.2], 1);]]></example_item_data>
                    </example_item>
